cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper investigates the impact of memory and storage on data-intensive workloads such as Hadoop, Spark, and MPI. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also analyzes the performance of these workloads in the presence of different storage types, which suggests a possible fit for cs.DB (Databases) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also discusses the impact of DRAM on the performance of these workloads, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
